cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of data augmentation for supervised training of automated medical image analysis systems. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel selection mechanism for synthetic images generated by conditional Adversarial Networks (cGANs), which is related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on natural image classification benchmarks, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
